\intbl \ql \b Background\b0 \line The All Nations Bible Institution and Projects is not yet registered with the Department of Higher Education and Training and has no programmes accredited by the CHE. In the Institutional Profile\'2C the Institution purports to be an \'22Existing institution\'22.\line \line The Institution applied for accreditation of the Doctor of Philosophy in Theology which was tabled at the AC meeting held on the 24th of November 2021 and HEQC meeting held on the 11th of February 2022.\line \line The programme was not accredited for the following reasons\'3A\line 1. The application has critical weaknesses in relation to criterion 1.\line 1.1 The vision of the Institution is not clear in terms of its educational\'2C developmental and\'2For research objectives. There is a lack of clarity on how the programme supports the academic and research aims of the Institution.\line 1.2 The programme does not meet the requirements of the HEQSF as it is neither a professional doctoral degree nor is it an education programme. The programme design is not appropriate for a professional doctoral degree and the rationale and purpose of the programme have not been provided.\line 1.3 The SAQA document has not been provided.\line 1.4 The programme includes WIL which is inappropriate since the programme is not designed as a professional doctorate. The submission also makes provision for 12 months of WIL placement with no credit allocation.\line 1.5 The CESM category allocated to the programme is incorrect.\line 2.1 The minimum admission requirements are not aligned with current legislation and are inappropriate for a doctoral degree. \line 2.2 The Institution does not have appropriate policies and procedures for the admission and selection of students\'2C nor for the selection and appointment of supervisors.\line 3.1 The submission failed to demonstrate that there are sufficient qualified staff to offer the programme and supervise research.\line 3.2 Administrative staff and HR policies are inadequate.\line 4.1 The Teaching and Learning Strategy is not suitable for a Doctoral programme.\line 4.2 The Institution has not provided evidence of academic support.\line 5. The Institution has failed to demonstrate that it has adequate policies and procedures regarding assessment.\line 6. No information on infrastructure or IT infrastructure was provided\'2C and no library resources are available.\line 7. The Institution did not provide evidence to substantiate its ability to offer and support postgraduate research.\line 8. The Institution failed to demonstrate its ability to offer higher education programmes via the distance mode of delivery.\line 9. The Institution did not demonstrate that it has adequate administrative services to manage and support the programme. \line 10. The institutional policies are inadequate\'2C and do not meet the expected standards for higher education.\line Note\'3A The submission and supporting documents include several instances of plagiarism.\line Note\'3A The institutional profile includes contradictory information\'2C e.g.\'2C the Institution reflects undergraduate enrolments\'2C while this is a new institution that is not registered as a higher education institution\'2C and does not offer other higher education programmes.\line \line The Institution submitted a representation which has been evaluated.\cell \pard 

